{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} '''European Information Technologies Certification Academy''' ('''EITCA''') programme is an international professional ICT knowledge and skills [[Professional certification (computer technology)|certification standard]], developed and governed by the [[European Information Technologies Certification Institute|EITCI Institute]] – a non-profit organization based in [[Brussels]], that provides certification of individuals' knowledge and skills in broad field-oriented areas of [[Information and communications technology|ICT]] expertise such as Computer graphics, Information security etc. The EITCA programmes, referred to as ''EITCA Academies'', include selected sets of several to over a dozen of individual [[European Information Technologies Certification|EITC]] programmes, that together comprise a particular area of qualifications.<ref name="csedu2014">{{cite conference |url=https://files.ifi.uzh.ch/stiller/CLOSER%202014/CSEDU/CSEDU/Learning/Teaching%20Methodologies%20and%20Assessment/Full%20Papers/CSEDU_2014_138_CR.pdf |title=The Elevate Framework for Assessment and Certification Design for Vocational Training in European ICT SMEs |conference=6th International Conference on Computer Supported Education (CSEDU 2014) |conference-url=http://www.csedu.org/?y=2014 |last1=Paraskakis |first1=Iraklis |last2=Hatziapostolou |first2=Thanos |date=2014 }}</ref><ref name="eitci_eitca">{{cite web |url=http://www.eitci.org/eitca-programme |title=EITCA programme|publisher=European Information Technologies Certification Institute (EITCI)}}</ref><ref name="ict2013">{{cite web |url=http://ec.europa.eu/digital-agenda/events/cf/ict2013/item-display.cfm?id=10661 |title=ICT training/education and certification |website=Digital Agenda for Europe, ICT 2013 |publisher=European Commission}}</ref><ref name="jacsm">{{cite journal|last1=Goetzen|first1=P.|last2=Chmielecki|first2=M.|last3=Hernes|first3=M.|title=Egovernment in Poland – Research on Polish Policies and Practices|journal=Journal of Applied Computer Science Methods|date=2012|volume=4|issue=2|pages=5–20|doi=10.2478/jacsm|url=http://yadda.icm.edu.pl/yadda/element/bwmeta1.element.baztech-85fc9fd0-80a6-48b2-84a4-62820e8e1bf2}}</ref>
