'''Samuel Mathiassen Føyn''' (2 November 1786 – 9 August 1854) was a Norwegian ship-owner and politician.
He was elected to the [[Storting|Norwegian Parliament]] in 1830, 1842 and 1848, representing the constituency of [[Tønsberg]]. He worked as a ship-owner, merchant and farmer in that city.<ref name="nsd">[http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=parliament&lan=eng&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=10888 Samuel Mathiassen Føyn] &mdash; Norwegian Social Science Data Services (NSD)</ref>
